quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  4,24,"Also ňĻforbidden areňļ married women‚ÄĒexcept ňĻfemaleňļ captives in your possession.¬†This is God‚Äôs commandment to you. Lawful to you are all beyond these‚ÄĒas long as you seek them with your wealth in a legal marriage, not in fornication. Give those you have consummated marriage with their due dowries. It is permissible to be mutually gracious regarding the set dowry. Surely God is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  4,25,"But if any of you cannot afford to marry a free believing woman, then ňĻlet him marryňļ a believing bondwoman possessed by one of you. God knows best ňĻthe state ofňļ your faith ňĻand theirsňļ. You are from one another.¬†So marry them with the permission of their owners,¬†giving them their dowry in fairness, if they are chaste, neither promiscuous nor having secret affairs. If they commit indecency after marriage, they receive half the punishment of free women.¬†This is for those of you who fear falling into sin. But if you are patient, it is better for you. And God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  4,26,"It is God‚Äôs Will to make things clear to you, guide you to the ňĻnobleňļ ways of those before you, and turn to you in mercy. For God is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  4,27,"And it is God‚Äôs Will to turn to you in grace, but those who follow their desires wish to see you deviate entirely ňĻfrom God‚Äôs Wayňļ"
  4,28,"And it is God‚Äôs Will to lighten your burdens, for humankind was created weak"
  4,29,"O believers! Do not devour one another‚Äôs wealth illegally, but rather trade by mutual consent. And do not kill ňĻeach other orňļ yourselves. Surely God is ever Merciful to you"
  4,30,"And whoever does this sinfully and unjustly, We will burn them in the Fire. That is easy for God"
  4,31,"If you avoid the major sins forbidden to you, We will absolve you of your ňĻlesserňļ misdeeds and admit you into a place of honour"
  4,32,"And do not crave what God has given some of you over others. Men will be rewarded according to their deeds and women ňĻequallyňļ according to theirs. Rather, ask God for His bounties. Surely God has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of all things"
  4,33,"And We have appointed heirs to what has been left by parents and next of kin. As for those you have made a pledge to, give them their share.¬†Surely God is a Witness over all things"
  4,34,"Men are the caretakers of women, as men have been provisioned by God over women and tasked with supporting them financially. And righteous women are devoutly obedient and, when alone, protective of what God has entrusted them with.¬†And if you sense ill-conduct from your women, advise them ňĻfirstňļ, ňĻif they persist,ňļ do not share their beds, ňĻbut if they still persist,ňļ then discipline them ňĻgentlyňļ.¬†But if they change their ways, do not be unjust to them. Surely God is Most High, All-Great"
  4,35,"If you anticipate a split between them, appoint a mediator from his family and another from hers. If they desire reconciliation, God will restore harmony between them. Surely God is All-Knowing, All-Aware"